ng friends is actually not that hard when you drop every single one of your standards.\n\n- Leila Sales, This Song Will Save Your Life\n|\nThe individual appears for an instant, joins the community of thought, modifies it and dies; but the species, that dies not, reaps the fruit of his ephemeral existence.\n\n- A.S. Byatt, Possession\n|\nin earth their have only one reason of war,i have power and want to show,\n\n- majidkhan\n|\nIf books had not bound together the experiences of former generations, the shackles of later generations in their forgetfulness would not have been loosed.\n\n- Mahbud\n|\nThere's always something when you're at fault, too, and that fault you must discover and learn to recognize and take the consequences of it.\n\n- Anne Holm, I Am David\n|\nWe learn from failure, not from success!\n\n- Bram Stoker, Dracula\n|\nWe make Idols of our concepts, but Wisdom is born of wonder\n\n- Pope\n|\nAlas, woman is faithful as long as she loves, but you demand that she be faithful without love and give herself without enjoyment. Who is cruel then, woman or man?\n\n- Leopold von Sacher-Masoch, Venus in Furs\n|\nI would rather carry around a plastic bag with five thousand Euro inside, than carry around a Louis Vuitton/Gucci/Prada bag with only one hundred Euro inside!\n\n- C.\n|\nThe point at which things happen is a decision. In stead of focusing on yourself, focus on how you can help someone else.\n\n- Germany\n|\nIf all the girls attending [the Yale prom] were laid end to end, I wouldn't be at all surprised.\n\n- Dorothy Parker, While Rome Burns\n|\nWhy destroy this Morn, by a Past that is dead & Gone and a Future not yet Born!\n\n- RVM\n|\nBeauty is truth, truth beauty\n\n- John Keats, Ode on a Grecian Urn and Other Poems\n|\nWe all know writing is a reclusive, lonely endeavour. It just is. But nobody writes alone.\n\n- Iain Reid, One Bird's Choice\n|\nNothing could be any worse than having to turn to your friends, your colleagues and your loved ones and say –‘I gave up too soon’.\n\n- Steve Backley, The Champion in all of Us: 12 Rules for Success\n|\nIt will hurt.' said Petra. 'But let's make the most of what we have, and not let future pain ruin present happiness.\n\n- Orson Scott Card, Shadow Puppets\n|\nThere are only three ways to teach a child. The first is by example, the second is by example, the third is by example.\n\n- Albert\n|\nCruel', O'Kelly laughed, 'it's cruel to tell children the truth. If anything convinces me of God's mercy, then it's his gift of making us unable to lie.\n\n- Yevgeny Zamyatin, Islanders And, The Fisher Of Men\n|\nI guess if I had to pick a spiritual figurehead to possess the deed to the entirety of Earth, I'd go with Buddha, but only because he wouldn't want it.\n\n- Sarah Vowell, Unfamiliar Fishes\n|\nIf you harden the soil, the seed cannot grow; if you harden your heart, the love cannot grow!\n\n- Mehmet\n|\nCelestial light, shine inward...that I may see and tell of things invisible to mortal sight\n\n- John\n|\nGenerosity is to help a deserving person without his request, and if you help him after hisrequest, then it is either out of self-respect or to avoid rebuke.\n\n- Hazrat\n|\nGuard yourself with a positive attitude, conviction, hope and fulfillment of your heart’s desire.\n\n- Sunday Adelaja, The Mountain of Ignorance\n|\nSparrows and cats will live in my shoe,Sooner than I will live with you.Fish will come walking out of the sea,Sooner than you will come back to me.\n\n- Peter S. Beagle, The Last Unicorn\n|\nLife's a wondrous journey, don't take it for granted.\n\n- Joseph\n|\nIgnite the light within you, it will make your world brighter.\n\n- Avis\n|\nYou don't need to understand what the world is, just let your life flow with it and become something\n\n- Jayson\n|\nI can think of few better ways to introduce a child to books than to let her stack them, upend them, rearrange them, and get her fingerprints all over them.\n\n- Anne Fadiman, Ex Libris: Confessions of a Common Reader\n|\nEmbrace lousy days. I’ve learned to remind myself easy days are part of the deal, and a great day is just around the corner.\n\n- Dan John, Never Let Go: A Philosophy of Lifting, Living and Learning\n|\nWhen two broken hearts meet, they find their missing part in each other.\n\n- Luffina\n|\nYour purpose lies where your passion, wisdom and gifts meet and complement each other.\n\n- Mensah\n|\nWhile the heart beats, hope lingers.\n\n- Alison\n|\nReading is like travel, allowing you to exit your own life for a bit, and to come back with a renewed, even inspired, perspective.\n\n- Laurie A. Helgoe, Introvert Power: Why Your Inner Life Is Your Hidden Strength\n|\nA thing is only as great as the amount a person is willing to risk for it. If you are not willing to risk anything, then the thing mustn't be so great at all.\n\n- Madeline Claire Franklin, The Poppet and the Lune\n|\nWhen you were in love, you knew no fear or hatred. When you were fearful, there was no possibility of love or hate. And when there was hate, there was only hate.\n\n- Christopher Pike, The Last Vampire\n|\nIn every department of physical science there is only so much science, properly so-called, as there is mathematics.\n\n- Immanuel\n|\nI want you. I want you so badly I can’t stand it. When you left, it felt like the world got darker. Like I couldn’t truly see anything. Couldn’t feel anything.\n\n- Rachel Vincent, Alpha\n|\nWe need hope, or else we cannot endure.\n\n- Sarah J. Maas, A Court of Thorns and Roses\n|\nBut magic is neither good nor evil. It is a tool, like a knife. Is a knife evil? Only if the wielder is evil.\n\n- Rick Riordan, The House of Hades\n|\nFor what is it to die but to stand naked in the wind and to melt into the sun? And when the earth shall claim your limbs, then shall you truly dance.\n\n- Kahlil\n|\nStop feeling sorry for yourself and get to work, your future lies ahead of you\n\n- Sid Mittra, To Bee or Not to Bee: Winning Against All Odds\n|\nWasn't writing a kind of soaring, an achievable form of flight, of fancy, of the imagination?\n\n- Ian McEwan, Atonement\n|\nEvery day People straighten up the hair, why not the heart?\n\n- Ernesto\n|\nYou were born for a purpose and a special reason.Your purpose identifies your passion, your potential, the source of your fulfilment in life, and ultimately your success\n\n- Mensah\n|\nYou're off to Great Places!Today is your day!Your mountain is waiting,So... get on your way!\n\n- Dr. Seuss, Oh, The Places You'll Go!\n|\nPoetry, plays, novels, music, they are the cry of the human spirit trying to understand itself and make sense of our world.\n\n- L.M. Elliott, Annie, Between the States\n|\nDeath, he had come to believe, was a corrosive thing, and the more he was around it , the more it gnawed away at who he was.\n\n- Christopher Paolini, Inheritance\n|\n..Breaking yet budding,dying yet living - standingamongst ruins and rage,reaching for possibilitiesplaying hard to get.\n\n- Meraaqi, Divine Trouble\n|\nFoolish men always believe that a little knowledge will give them control over the world, but it is no more than a display of their vanity.\n\n- J. P. Vinluca, Aiko and the Dragon\n|\nThere's nothing wrong with stretching the truth. We stretch taffy, and that just makes it more delicious.\n\n- Stephen\n|\nGrief is an amputation, but hope is incurable haemophilia: you bleed and bleed and bleed. Like Schrödinger’s cat inside a box you can never ever open.\n\n- David Mitchell, Slade House\n|\nFor books are more than books, they are the life, the very heart and core of ages past, the reason why men worked and died, the essence and quintessence of their lives.\n\n- Marcus\n|\nSome people have a way with words, and other people...oh, uh, not have way.\n\n- Steve\n|\nAll bad poetry springs from genuine feeling. To be natural is to be obvious, and to be obvious is to be inartistic.\n\n- Oscar\n|\nIf you're a writer, write. And always strive for excellence.\n\n- Linda\n|\nYour thinking